\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection
Algorithmic implementation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have decided to use 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "tm"
target "https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/tm/tm.pdf"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 and
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name " tidytext"
target "https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/tidytext/tidytext.pdf"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 libraries for perfoming the tf-idf calculation.
 We have calculated the tf-idf for each title offline, the text elements
 were the concatenation of the title and the description of each project.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
After computing the tf-idf we have decided to extract the ten with the higher
 score and calculate the average tf-idf among the documents, computing the
 scatter plot plotting the average versus the number of tittles in which
 it appears.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Conclusions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We chose this dataset because we were interested in knowing more about Horizon
 2020 and the projects involved on it.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It has been challenging afterwards the process of thinking in which way
 we could contribute more to the current web CORDIS has available and the
 process of transforming the dataset available in order to fit the requirements
 we came up with.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It could be interesting to maintain the code and try to use the next data
 available for the following projects regarding research and innovation
 in the EU.
\end_layout

